Job Description:
Booking.com’s global treasury team is looking for a  Treasury risk management professional to join our growing team. 
The Treasury Risk Specialist is responsible for performing financial analysis and operating processes relating to the identification, quantification, management and reporting of credit, counterparty, liquidity and other Treasury risk typologies that attach to Booking’s evolving business models, strategic initiatives and third party relationships.  
The individual will form an integral part of the Treasury Risk Team, reporting to the Treasury Manager for this function.  
The preferred candidate should be accustomed to working in a fast paced environment while working collaboratively across various internal functional teams.
The candidate should be able to demonstrate a proven ability to perform risk analysis and reporting and drive operational efficiencies through the design and implementation of End to End processes leveraging and adopting new technologies to support best in class risk management and reporting.
Characteristics of a successful candidate include strong analytical skills and experience of adopting and implementing advanced analytics as a means of making data driven recommendations to complex problems.
A successful candidate should possess excellent communication and organisational skills and be able to partner with stakeholders of various levels of seniority across the organisation, demonstrating strong business judgement skills while being able to think creatively and strategically.
Due to the continuous growth of the organization, the tasks and duties of this role will evolve over time. You will be keen to develop and grow within the role and challenge yourself to take on additional projects and responsibilities as they present themselves.
  B.Responsible:
Produce high quality assessments and reports addressing credit and counterparty risk for Financial Institutions & Fintech Partners, Investment related activities, and Trip Providers for senior management, steering committees and internal stakeholders;
Support fundamental credit and counterparty risk assessments for new product and third party relationships, providing recommendations based on relative value assessments:
Leverage available technologies and tooling to quantify risk exposures, perform both ad hoc and cyclical credit and financial analysis across applicable counterparty portfolios;
Responsible for the ongoing operations and maintenance of our Treasury Risk Management System and ensure the data quality and reporting accuracy while seeking continuous efficiency improvements; 
Manage the credit limits assigned to Financial Institutions and monitor the breaches to the assigned limit. Work with stakeholders to manage the breaches on a periodic basis and to develop optimal limit management techniques;
Ongoing monitoring and maintenance of system based compliance rules for Investment Programs;
Maintain existing risk models, calculate risk scores and quantify the expected loss for applicable counterparties;
Maintain and ensure operational compliance with FX regulations(Dodd Frank and EMIR); 
Perform system based VAR calculations and MTM assessment for FX hedging programs; 
Perform required analysis to support interest rate determinations for Intercompany Lending arrangements.;
Own the existing quarterly process and controls  to determine lease discount rates for leases denominated in different currencies;
Seek to enhance/automate the current reporting mechanisms to effectively monitor the risk exposures, maintain the risk profile for all counterparties, leveraging key technology enablers, such as Clearwater, Reval, S&P Capital IQ, Bloomberg, SAP S/4.
Continuously liaise with key stakeholders across the business to understand business priorities, and requirements and identify associated risks to support with business decisions;
Develop strong business relationships with key  internal stakeholders across Finance, Legal, Tax, Product teams and other cross functional teams.
  B.Skilled:
A proven professional track record of 3-5 years and relevant experience gained within a Treasury, Banking or related field;
Masters’ degree in a related field (Finance, Statistics, Economics or related degrees)
Specific expertise in the credit and counterparty risk management techniques; 
Demonstrated analytical skills for determining, evaluating and quantifying counterparty risk exposures - advanced Excel skills and financial modeling skills are necessary;
Proven experience in using and maintaining complex financial models;
Ability to work autonomous on reporting, risk monitoring and implementing risk related E2E processes and controls;
Broad knowledge of various risk typologies, such as FX, investment and liquidity risk. 
Broad knowledge of micro and macroeconomic factors, with the ability to translate these into risk-based decisions;
Experience with Clearwater, Reval, S&P Capital IQ, Bloomberg, SAP S/4 is a plus
Knowledge of SQL, Python, R and/ or other statistical and advanced programming language is a plus;
Problem solving ability aligned with high attention to detail;
Excellent analytical, organisational and project management skills 
Self-starter and able to work with minimal supervision;
Ability to prioritize tasks and meet required deadlines while managing competing priorities and working within a faced paced environment;
Excellent communication skills (both written and verbal) in English and ability to effectively convey difficult or complex information in an easy to understandable manner while adapting style and approach based on the seniority of applicable stakeholders
  B.offered
We are a performance-based company that offers career advancement and lucrative compensation, including bonus. We also offer what is called the “Booking Deal” with competitive benefits. This position is open to any candidate globally and in the case of relocation, we will assist you with a generous relocation package, ensuring a smooth transition to working and living in The Netherlands.

