User Research & Insights Specialist
  This is a unique opportunity for an experienced user researcher to join the Insights team within Global Marketing at Booking.com. Booking.com is on a mission to make it easier for everyone to experience the world. We are a truly global e-commerce company, with business operations in nearly every country and city on the planet. And we want to make it easy for everyone, anywhere in the world, to pay for their travel or do business with our platform – whenever and however it’s convenient for them. Our global teams are constantly focused on developing and improving our product and marketing communications to empower consumers to experience the world. 
  The Insights team is responsible for delivering best-in-class market research and consumer insights to improve Booking.com’s global marketing strategy and communications. Within the Insights team you will lead UX research studies across the Marketing Department. You partner with the Insights team to understand consumers  - and how we can improve their experiences. You would play a key role in uncovering powerful consumer insights for all our marketing channels (including Messaging, Partnerships, PR & Social, Rewards & Incentives and Performance marketing) by conducting UX research. Your work inspires cross-functional partners on current product improvements and informs new products, to further improve our brand and product experience across all touchpoints.
  The role best suits someone who has strong experience (4+ years) with primary UX research methods, primary research (ex. usertesting, surveys, diary studies and interviews) as well as secondary research & expert methods (such as literature reviews, cognitive walkthroughs and desk research). You will lead UX research studies across the Marketing Department. You are a strong and empathetic partner within the research craft community and an experienced communicator and experienced in facilitating and leading workshops and engaging with stakeholders.

B.responsible:
Plan and conduct independent end-to-end UX research to collect and analyze customer behavior through a variety of qualitative and/or quantitative methods; 
Manage all aspects of research projects;
Connect disparate data points across consumer insights and other business data to illustrate the “big picture” - including internal and external secondary research;
Be the users' advocate, ensuring their needs are central to design and development decisions of product concepts, comms and brand touchpoints;
Uncover actionable insights based on the research and translate them into strategic recommendations that influence key business decisions;
Collaborate with other researchers in the product organization (Marketing and Accommodations and Trips Business Unit), affinity with B2B research
Present and socialize research findings across different departments at all levels of the organization (especially to non-researchers); explore new ways of sharing research results and engaging stakeholders;
Lead and facilitate research and consumers insights workshops;
Develop strong working relationships throughout the business and external agencies (research panels, recruitment agencies, media buying and creative agencies);
A team player with a self-starting approach, you must have gravitas and the ability to get things done;
Improve and innovate our existing research processes and methodologies, explore new ways of gathering consumer insights through innovative research tools such as online community panels, remote testing, and conversational research.
  B.skilled
We are looking for an experienced UX researcher with a track record gained at a leading agency or an e-commerce environment. You will bring strategic thinking, passion and inspiration to your role. Key skills and experience include the following:
A proven track record of 4+ years as a UX researcher, preferably focusing on topics related to brand touchpoints, communications as well as product concepts; 
Lives and breathes UX research; extremely well-versed in designing and executing various forms of research aimed at guiding business decision-making; 
Experience with designing, leading and implementing UX Research projects with a great degree of autonomy; 
Knowledge and practical experience of using a variety of UX research methods (qualitative and quantitative), with a strong awareness of their merits and weaknesses;
Experience of using a variety of commercial UX Research or VOC software tools; 
Able to identify which research method is best suited to a given business and research objective; 
Strong communication skills, both written and verbally (a true storyteller); 
A real team player with solutions-focus and entrepreneurial spirit; 
Excellent organizational skills with ability to manage multiple, competing priorities simultaneously and deliver results under tight deadlines; 
Fluency in English both spoken and written; additional fluency in one other language, e.g. German, French or Spanish, is a plus;
Master Degree or higher degree in psychology, social or behavioural sciences, economics or similar.
