The B2B Partner Experience Insights Senior Specialist position is responsible for contributing to the voice of partner program for all our key business partner audiences (supply, demand, technology and industry).
This role supports the B2B Partner Experience Insights Manager to ensure that Booking.com has a robust understanding of our partners’ sentiment at a macro brand and micro touchpoint level, including how we are trending over time. 
They collaborate with the B2B Partner Experience Insights Manager and Research colleagues to design methodologies that enable us to effectively capture and interpret partner sentiment data, and help implement these methodologies across a variety of channels and touch points via our CX tooling.
This role compares claimed and behavioural data to identify and illuminate correlations between how our partners think and feel, and how they act. This in turn supports the business to understand the commercial implications of partner sentiment, in order to inform investment decisions. 
B.Responsible:
Support the Director B2B Marketing Communications and B2B Partner Experience Insights Manager to design and deliver the voice of partner program for all key business partner audiences (supply, demand, technology and industry);
Help ensure that key Booking.com stakeholders, including Leadership, have a robust understanding of our partners’ sentiment at a macro brand and micro touchpoint level;
Collaborate with the B2B Partner Experience Insights Manager and Research colleagues to help design methodologies that enable us to effectively capture and interpret partner sentiment data;
Support the B2B Partner Experience Insights Manager to implement partner experience research methodologies across a variety of channels and touch points via our CX tooling;
Compare claimed and behavioural data to identify and illuminate correlations between how our partners think and feel, and how they act;
Support the business to understand the commercial implications of partner sentiment, in order to inform investment decisions;
Turn partner sentiment data into clear, compelling reporting and actionable insights for (senior) stakeholders across the business
Support the Director: B2B Marketing Communications and B2B Partner Experience Insights Manager to define the overarching B2B Partner Experience strategy and socialise it across the business;
Develop collaborative partnerships across the business in order to identify and execute on partner experience optimisation opportunities, delivering measurable positive impact on partner sentiment and satisfaction;
Collaborate with Research to understand and leverage existing partner experience insights and generate new ones, in order to deliver partner experience optimisation strategies which meet B2B partner needs and wants. 
B.Skilled:
3+ years experience in a relevant role;
Strong technical data skills, statistics and the ability to draw business insights from data;
Data-driven, has technical affinity and possesses a strong business sense;
2+ years of hands-on experience in Tableau, defining reporting landscape across several layers of an organisation;
Knowledge and awareness of at least one data analysis/query language (e.g.: R, SQL, Python, etc);
Excellent communication and story-telling skills (verbal, dashboarding and written);
Ability to convey complex analysis results clearly and with conviction to all levels of stakeholders;
Excellent organisational skills, attention to detail and analytical reasoning;
Experience working with CX measurement tools (e.g. Qualtrics, Survey Gizmo and/or Hotjar) is a plus.

